from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
topo = "tree4"
df = pd.read_csv("topo_" + topo + ".csv")

x = df["Timestamp"]
y1 = df['Uso de memória (MiB)']
y2 = df['% de uso de CPU']

colors = [
    'tab:red',
    'tab:blue'
]

# Plot Line1 (Left Y Axis)
fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, figsize=(16,9), dpi= 200)
ax[0].plot(x, y1, linewidth=4, color=colors[0])
ax[1].plot(x, y2, linewidth=4, color=colors[1])


ax[0].set_title('Uso de memória (Max 300 MiB)', pad=10, fontsize=20)
ax[0].set_ylabel("MiB", labelpad =40, rotation=0, color=colors[0], fontsize=20)
ax[0].tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor=colors[0], labelsize=20 )
ax[0].tick_params(left = True, right = False , labelleft = True , labelbottom = False, bottom = False)


ax[1].set_title('Uso de CPU (Max 400%)', pad=10, fontsize=20)
ax[1].set_ylabel("%", labelpad =40, rotation=0, color=colors[1], fontsize=20)
ax[1].tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor=colors[1], labelsize=20 )
ax[1].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=25, labelsize=12)

ax[1].set_xlabel('Tempo', fontsize=20)

for i in range(2):
    ax[i].axvline(x="19:18:26", linewidth=2.5, color='purple', linestyle=':', label='Execução da Topologia')
    ax[i].axvline(x="19:18:40", linewidth=2.5, color='blue',  linestyle='-.', label='Execução do pingall')
    ax[i].grid(alpha=.4)

plt.subplots_adjust(bottom=0.1, hspace=0.2)
fig.tight_layout()
fig.savefig("plots/" + topo + ".png")
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Import libraries
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
 
import pandas as pd
memoryStr = 'Uso de memória (MiB)'
cpuStr = '% de uso de CPU'

single2DF = pd.read_csv("topo_single2.csv")
single8DF = pd.read_csv("topo_single8.csv")
single16DF = pd.read_csv("topo_single16.csv")
single24DF = pd.read_csv("topo_single24.csv")

data = [[
  single2DF[memoryStr], 
  single8DF[memoryStr], 
  single16DF[memoryStr], 
  single24DF[memoryStr]
],
[
  single2DF[cpuStr], 
  single8DF[cpuStr], 
  single16DF[cpuStr], 
  single24DF[cpuStr]
]]
fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, figsize=(16,9), dpi= 200)
fig = plt.figure()
 
for i in range(2):
  bp = ax[i].boxplot(data[i])

for ax_ in ax:
  ax_.set_xlabel('xlabel')
  ax_.set_ylabel('ylabel')
  ax_.set_xticks([1, 2, 3, 4], ['Single 2', 'Single 8', 'Single 16', 'Single 24'])

fig.savefig("plots/singleboxplot.png")
plt.show()
